			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Catalytic oxidizers, also known as catalytic incinerators, are oxidation systems used to control VOC (Volatile Organic Compounds) and volatile HAP (Hazardous Air Pollutants) emissions. They utilize a catalyst to promote the oxidation of VOCs into carbon dioxide (CO2) and water, thereby increasing the kinetic rate of the reaction. </common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">催化氧化炉又称催化焚化炉，是一种氧化系统，用于控制 VOC（挥发性有机化合物）和挥发性 HAP（有害空气污染物）的排放。它们利用催化剂促进 VOC 氧化成二氧化碳（CO2）和水，从而提高反应的动力学速率。</common:generalComment>
